<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1365,2005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1365,1392]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[293,394,1367,1393]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,394,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jangoux, M." box="[707,881,1366,1393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" pagination="279 - 293" refId="ref24453" refString="Jangoux, M. (1984) Les asterides littoraux de Nouvelle-Caledonie. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Series 4, 6 A (Zoologie, Biologie et Ecologie animale), 2, 279 - 293." type="journal article" year="1984">Jangoux (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and tentatively assigned to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viguier" authorityYear="1878" box="[1229,1366,1366,1392]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Solasteridae</taxonomicName>
based on the shape of the actinal plates as compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sladen" authorityYear="1889" box="[720,851,1402,1428]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Rhipidaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,851,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Rhipidaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and abactinal plates from other solasterids including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sladen" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,352,1438,1464]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Solaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis box="[151,352,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Solaster regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1878" box="[406,520,1438,1464]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Lophaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,520,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Lophaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jangoux, M." box="[534,709,1438,1465]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" pagination="279 - 293" refId="ref24453" refString="Jangoux, M. (1984) Les asterides littoraux de Nouvelle-Caledonie. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Series 4, 6 A (Zoologie, Biologie et Ecologie animale), 2, 279 - 293." type="journal article" year="1984">Jangoux (1984)</bibRefCitation>
also pointed out affinities between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[1108,1209,1439,1465]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1209,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1840" box="[1263,1386,1438,1464]" class="Asteroidea" family="Chaetasteridae" genus="Chaetaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1263,1386,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Chaetaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1365,2005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">
Examination of the adambulacral plates in both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[746,847,1475,1501]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[746,847,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viguier" authorityYear="1878" box="[1089,1226,1474,1500]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Solasteridae</taxonomicName>
revealed that they are distinctly different. Solasterids, using 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sladen" authorityYear="1889" box="[621,752,1510,1536]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Rhipidaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[621,752,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Rhipidaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the exemplar (
<figureCitation box="[952,1020,1510,1536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,183,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,174,1889]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Paralophaster gomo n. sp. Holotype, NSMT-E-11294. Scale bar=0.5 cm for all except B and C. A. Abactinal surface. B. Closeup of abactinal surface. Scale bar=2.0 mm. C. Oral surface. Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Closeup of oral region. E. Small specimen showing large primary plates NMST E-11260." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702851/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), possess a wide adambulacral plate, each separated from the other plates by a distinct tissue filled space.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1365,2005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[199,300,1583,1609]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,300,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in contrast, lacks the large, wide transversely arranged adambulacral plate with the broad round facet and tissue-filled space between plates and has instead smaller more block-shape adambulacral plates present in a transverse series with each adambulacral plate facing separated by a small tissue-filled space (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1373,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1938,1963]" captionTargetBox="[219,1371,173,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[210,1378,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 10. Seriaster regularis. NSMT-E-10637. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=0.5 cm. B. Close-up of abactinal paxillae. Scale bar=1.0 mm. C. Oral surface. Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Close-up of tube foot furrow and adambulacral plates. Scale bar=1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702865" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702865/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). The adambulacral plates are abutted directly onto the adjacent inferomarginal, which in turn was in contact with the the parallel superomarginal plate. Both marginal plate series followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, D. B." box="[903,1070,1726,1752]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" pagination="234 - 241" refId="ref22895" refString="Blake, D. B. (1978) The taxonomic position of the modern sea-star Cistina Gray, 1840. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 91 (1), 234 - 241." type="journal article" year="1978">Blake’s (1978)</bibRefCitation>
definition for marginal plates in which the series tracks from the interradius to the arm terminus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1365,2005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[199,300,1799,1825]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,300,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also possesses abactinal plates in ordered imbricate series forming regular papular pores sitting between paxillae-like plates, exhibit hyaline spinelets on the abactinals and lacks the abactinal skeleton structure observed in solasterids, including the reticular, irregular skeleton observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sladen" authorityYear="1889" box="[907,1038,1870,1896]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Rhipidaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[907,1038,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Rhipidaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or the paxillae-like plates sitting on round, imbricate plates observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1878" box="[552,666,1906,1932]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Lophaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,666,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Lophaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1365,2005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">
Our skeletal observations disagree with the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jangoux" authorityYear="1984" box="[857,958,1943,1969]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" genus="Seriaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[857,958,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="93">Seriaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viguier" authorityYear="1878" box="[1091,1228,1942,1968]" class="Asteroidea" family="Solasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="93" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Solasteridae</taxonomicName>
made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jangoux, M." pageId="26" pageNumber="93" pagination="279 - 293" refId="ref24453" refString="Jangoux, M. (1984) Les asterides littoraux de Nouvelle-Caledonie. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Series 4, 6 A (Zoologie, Biologie et Ecologie animale), 2, 279 - 293." type="journal article" year="1984">Jangoux (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and are more consistent with placement within the Hyalinothricinae.
</paragraph>
